comment.author: 15828730@N05
comment._content:
I think a review of this photo by the good folks at the San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive may well be in order.  I believe this is a Focke-Wulf TA-152 and I have found a photo of this same fighter with the identical tail number on "The Military Factory" website so identified. 

Having said this I've got to add that the similarities between this machine and the Focke-Wulf FW 190 D-9 (the airframe that was used to develop the TA 152) make correct identification a chore.

comment.author: 49487266@N07
comment._content: [http://www.flickr.com/photos/15828730@N05] I believe you are correct.  Thank you very much!
